<p>I am starting on a <strong>Dashboard</strong> where Angular and React is used on the Client side while Node js is used as the Server side.</p>  <p>I was going through some architecture and i found this: </p>  <p><strong>View:</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;html ng-app="my-dashboard"&gt;   &lt;body&gt;     &lt;div class="Some structuring thing"&gt;       &lt;ng-include src="my-header.html"&gt;&lt;/ng-include&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;div class="Some other thing"&gt;       &lt;ng-include src="my-sidebar.html"&gt;&lt;/ng-include&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;      etc...    &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>Controllers:</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;div ng-controller="my-header-text"&gt;   &lt;p ng-bind="title"&gt;    etc... &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div ng-controller="my-header-login"&gt;   &lt;p ng-click="login()"&gt;Login&lt;/p&gt;    etc...  &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>From these pieces of code, <strong>is it possible to pave way for an app similar to <a href="http://angularsignalrdashboardlouiebacaj.azurewebsites.net/index.html#" rel="nofollow">this</a>?</strong></p>  <p>Thanks.</p>